This paper deals with the analysis of strategic games, which is a central topic in game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also discusses the reasoning of players, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with intelligent agents and their decision-making processes. The paper also presents an axiomatic presentation, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of public announcements, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which deal with communication and distributed systems.
